text=(:title Message length indicator:)%0a%3c|[[TabSRMM.#reference#endreference|Page Index]]|>%0a= Message length handling in TabSRMM =%0a[[#teaser]]%0aAll IM protocols have a maximum amount of characters (or, more precisely, bytes) that can be sent in a single message. Usually, that value is enforced by the protocol and there is no way around the limit. To make things more complex, the message length limit is not always the same. For example, the ICQ protocol enforces different limits for online and offline message - you can send much bigger messages to online contacts than you can send to offline contacts.%0a[[#teaserend]]\\\%0a(:include Template/Formatting#rimage#endrimage Image="Message_length_indicator.png" Width=400 Caption="Visual message length indicator":)%0aThe message window plugin should respect that value and should not let the user enter messages exceeding that limit, because in that case, the user would receive an error when trying to send a message that is too large.\\\%0a%0aTabSRMM uses the limit to enforce the maximum amount of characters you can type in the message input field. It also shows you in the status bar the current message length. If you hover the second status bar field (the field which shows the length) TabSRMM will show you a small tool tip with more information about the message size limit. This feature requires the presence of a mTooltip compatible plugin (tipper will do the job fine).%0a%0a(:include Template/Formatting#note#endnote Text="When the '''[[auto split]]''' option is enabled, TabSRMM will allow you to enter messages longer than the protocol's size limit. Such messages will be sent in multiple chunks, each chunk as a separate message up to a hardcoded limit of 20.000 characters which should be WAY more than ever needed for an instant message.":)%0a%0a== Visual message length indicator ==%0a%0aWhen you right click the message input area, the context menu will offer you the option to enable or disable the '''Message length indicator'''. This is only available for instant messaging sessions (not chat rooms) and requires a visible status bar. If the status bar is disabled, the option will be grayed out.%0a%0aThis indicator will appear as a tiny green bar on the bottom of the leftmost status bar field and will grow to the right while you enter text. It shows the length of your message compared to the message length limit%0a%0aWhen '''[[auto split]]''' is enabled, the bar will change its appearance somewhat. The leftmost (green) part will show the length relative to the maximum supported message length while an optional (red colored) part on the right will show up, when your message is too long to be sent in a single chunk. So, if you see this red colored bar, it means that TabSRMM will have to split the message into two or more chunks before sending it.%0a%0a
